                        <ab type="script">Fine</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>The Ms. was written in the same hand as
                        AP-064. The handwriting is similar, but not identical to that of
                           AP-038.<date>Late 17th-18th century</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The hand is the same as that of AP-064
                        and is similar to that of AP-038. The handwriting is characterized by a fine
                        script with tendency to slender, right-sloping, angular letters.
                        <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Some distinctive features appear
                        throughout the
                        Ms.:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> - archaic form of 'one' (፩, triangular
                        upwards-oriented)<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic"> - short hairlines extending horizontal
                        elements of some letters (esp., የ and ይ
                        )<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic"> - strongly pronounced shading (esp. መ,
                        በ, ን, ዘ, የ,
                        ደ)<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic"> - some letters have extremities with
                        forked ends (esp. ኃ, ር, ን, ገ,
                        ጋ)<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic"> - the hook vowel marker of ቱ is
                        attached at the upper part of the
                        downstroke<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h9" script="Ethiopic"> - ክ shows a very distinct vowel
                        marker<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h10" script="Ethiopic"> - the right loop of ሠ (in all vowel
                        orders) is of a very small
                        size<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h11" script="Ethiopic"> - letters ደ and ይ appear in a
                        triangular
                        shape<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h12" script="Ethiopic"> - ጥ is written with long
